In order to use the Kayenta GeoModel with Uintah, you will need to
do the following:

1.  Access the Kayenta, aka GeoModel, source code.  See Jim Guilkey
or Rebecca Brannon for more information on this.

2.  In the trunk/demo/source_030626 directory, do:

make uintah

Which will create a UintahKayenta000000 directory (where 000000 stands for the
build date in yymmdd form), which will contain the relevant source code.

3.  From the directory you are currently in
(Uintah/CCA/Components/MPM/ConstitutiveModel/fortran), do the following:

cp PATH_TO_KAYENTA/trunk/demo/source_030626/UintahKayenta000000/*.F .
cp PATH_TO_KAYENTA/trunk/demo/source_030626/UintahKayenta000000/*.h .
cp PATH_TO_KAYENTA/trunk/demo/source_030626/UintahKayenta000000/Kayenta_pnt.Blk .
cp PATH_TO_KAYENTA/trunk/demo/source_030626/UintahKayenta000000/geojoint_stiff.x .

At this point, you should be able to recompile the sus executable, after
which you will be ready to run simulations using Kayenta.
